# TGS Flow Sprint 1 Validation PRD

## Purpose

This document intentionally contains the minimum information required to validate that TGS Flow can automatically generate Jira backlog items from a structured planning artifact.

The validation confirms that a single Epic and a single Story can be created and linked through the TGS Flow backlog generation workflow.

---

# Problem

Engineering teams frequently begin work in GitHub without first updating Jira.  
This creates several operational issues:

• Work in progress is not visible to delivery leadership  
• Jira reporting becomes inaccurate  
• Engineers must perform manual updates later  
• Portfolio reporting loses alignment with actual engineering activity  

TGS Flow aims to reduce this friction by automatically reconciling GitHub activity with Jira tracking.

---

# Goal

Validate that TGS Flow can generate Jira backlog items from a simple planning document and that GitHub activity can be reflected automatically in Jira.

---

# Scope

This validation test will confirm the following capabilities:

• Generate a single Jira Epic from this document  
• Generate one Jira Story under that Epic  
• Assign the Story to an engineer  
• Link GitHub commits to the Jira Story through issue key references  
• Confirm Jira activity updates automatically when GitHub work occurs

